# Walkthrough: EfficientNet-B3 Baseline Implementation

## What Was Built

A complete, research-grade EfficientNet-B3 baseline pipeline for breast cancer histopathology classification on the **BreakHis dataset**, supporting both **binary** (Benign vs Malignant) and **3-class** (IDC, ILC, Fibroadenoma) tasks.

## Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [dataset.py](file:///d:/Projects/AI-Projects/Brest_cancer/src/data/dataset.py) | BreakHis loader with **patient-level GroupShuffleSplit** (70/15/15) — prevents data leakage |
| [efficientnet.py](file:///d:/Projects/AI-Projects/Brest_cancer/src/models/efficientnet.py) | Pretrained EfficientNet-B3 with replaced classifier head |
| [metrics.py](file:///d:/Projects/AI-Projects/Brest_cancer/src/utils/metrics.py) | Accuracy, F1, AUC (macro OVR), confusion matrix, ROC plots, FLOPs, inference time, CSV export |
| [train.py](file:///d:/Projects/AI-Projects/Brest_cancer/src/train.py) | Full training loop: mixed precision, AdamW, CosineAnnealingLR, AUC-based early stopping |
| [requirements.txt](file:///d:/Projects/AI-Projects/Brest_cancer/requirements.txt) | All dependencies including `ptflops`, `seaborn`, `scikit-learn` |
| [README.md](file:///d:/Projects/AI-Projects/Brest_cancer/README.md) | Usage guide with design decisions table |

## Key Design Choices (per mentor feedback)

- **Patient-level split** via `GroupShuffleSplit` — no patient overlaps between train/val/test
- **CrossEntropyLoss** for both tasks (binary mapped as 2-class)
- **Early stopping monitors Validation AUC**, not loss
- **CSV logs** include: Best Epoch, Total Training Time, GPU Memory, Inference Time
- **Seeds fixed** (`torch`, `numpy`, `random` = 42) + `cudnn.benchmark = True`

## How To Run

```bash
# 1. Install
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 2. Sanity check (do this first!)
python src/train.py --task binary --data_dir <PATH> --subset 200 --epochs 3

# 3. Full binary run
python src/train.py --task binary --data_dir <PATH>

# 4. Full 3-class run
python src/train.py --task multi --data_dir <PATH>
```

